    <h1>THE SE&#xAD;CRET ROOM OF BESTIARY</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200904/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-04"><time>2020-09-04</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>The cir­cuit breaker pe­riod was a dif­fi­cult time for many. Dancers from Arts Fission chan­nelled their frus­tra­tion into art – and the up­shot is this DIY dance pro­duc­tion (left), filmed on iPhones in their re­spec­tive homes.</p>
    <p>The work draws on the idea of a me­di­ae­val bestiary. Dancers Ti­tisa Jeam­sakul, Aisha Josephine, Delia</p>
    <p>Tan and Wang Wei Wei – from</p>
    <p>Thai­land, the Philip­pines, Sin­ga­pore and China – were in­spired by beasts from their re­spec­tive cul­tures and worked re­motely with artis­tic di­rec­tor An­gela Liong.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Sis­tic Live stream</p>
    <p>WHEN: To­mor­row and Sun­day,</p>
    <p>Sept 12 and 13 AD­MIS­SION: $10</p>
    <p>INFO: sis­tic.com.sg/events/ slse­cret0920</p>

